  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      SPINAL anesthesia is commonly used for cesarean section, and it has become a popular practice
      to add opioids to spinal solutions to enhance and prolong intraoperative and postoperative
      analgesia. high incidence of side effects was noted. is there any alternative?
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
